

======================================================
        Financial App - Setup and Installation Guide
======================================================

Introduction
------------
The Financial App is a static web application built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. 
It includes features such as profile management, credit pages, chat, and AI-based 
interaction. This guide will walk you through the process of setting up and running 
the app from the GitHub repository.

Prerequisites
-------------
Before you begin, make sure you have the following installed:
1. A modern web browser (Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox, Microsoft Edge, etc.).
2. Git (to clone the repository) - https://git-scm.com/
3. A code editor (e.g. Visual Studio Code).
4. A local web server (recommended for smooth usage). Options include:
   - VS Code Live Server extension
   - Node.js with `http-server`
5. Python 
6. Pip

Getting the Source Code
-----------------------
There are two ways to get the project files:

Option 1: Clone with Git (Recommended)
1. Open a terminal or command prompt.
2. Navigate to the directory where you want the project saved.
3. Run the command:
       git clone <repository_url>
4. Enter the new project folder:
       cd financial-app

Option 2: Download as ZIP
1. Go to the GitHub repository page in your browser.
2. Click on the green "Code" button, then select "Download ZIP".
3. Extract the ZIP file to your chosen location.

File Structure
--------------
After cloning or downloading, you will see the following structure:

financial app/
    home.html
    credit.html
    profile.html
    bio.html
    Aichat.html
    chat.html
    *.css   (stylesheets)
    *.js    (JavaScript files)
    *.png, *.jpg, *.webp (images and logos)

Installation Steps
------------------

Step 1: Open the Project
- Navigate to the cloned or extracted "financial app" folder.

Step 2: Quick Start (Direct Open)
- Double-click on "home.html" to open it in your browser.
- Note: Some features may not work properly without a local server.

Step 3: Run with VS Code Live Server (Recommended`	)
1. Install Visual Studio Code (if not already installed).
2. Open the project folder in VS Code.
3. Install the "Live Server" extension from the VS Code marketplace.
4. Right-click on "home.html" and select "Open with Live Server".
5. Your browser will open the app at: http://127.0.0.1:5500/

Usage
-----
Once the app is running, you can navigate through its different pages:(Note: Since we had make it according to mobile first application so it would recommended that you keep the dimensions or the responsiveness to that of iPhone SE )
- home.html      : Main landing page
- credit.html    : Credit management
- profile.html   : User profile
- bio.html       : Bio and information
- Aichat.html    : AI chat interface
- chat.html      : General chat page

ChatBox Guide
-------------

To use the functionality of chatbot 
unzip the chatbot folder
you will get a set of files copy it in same way as it will be in the folder to your IDE(Visiual Studio Recommended)
Python and pip should be installed in your device to mantain the flow the chatbot
Go to server.py file 
open your terminal and run the command
pip install -r requirements.txt
After the necessary packages are installed 
Run the command:
python server.py
There you will get two ports click on any one of them 
Set Your Screen Size to IPhone SE dimensions
And There is fully functional Chatbot Write your query and click send button

Conclusion
----------
You have successfully set up the Financial App from GitHub on your system. 
Enjoy exploring its features and functionalities!

